items.name: Aniwave
items.description:
💚 for Updates - I would love to see your reviews and images of this model, feel free to post them below!

Info

ℹ Some of the preview images of this model were accidently posted with another model file due to a webUI bug that used the wrong model while testing. Due to that I decided to use this page and post this early version for the time being to correct that mistake. I do have other variations of this model as well that I plan to post once sorted and finalized.

A versatile anime style model blended with a wave of semi-realistic tones through detailing, lighting, textures, and other aspects of the composition. Great with portraits, scenery/landscapes, and more!

This model currently has a somewhat rich 'heavier' style regarding some aspects and lighting details that I don't care for as much fully which feels a bit overbearing sometimes. Though with that said, there are also some very creative aspects you may find enjoyable for this model.

Recommended Use

I have limited testing with this model, however this one seems fairly easy to use. Use what works best for you - take a look at the preview and gallery images for some configuration examples. Based on the testing I have done, you may want to start simple with light/moderate values to avoid any overbearing styling and go from there. This includes cfg scale, denoising strength, etc. Choose whichever sampler(s) works best.

~20 steps, 7 scale, ~0.3-0.5 denoising, clip skip 1 or 2, is a good starting point

Use whichever vae you find best. Included is a renamed vae-ft-ema-560000-ema vae.

Note: this version/model is not finetuned to maximum detail accuracy.

Disclaimer

This model(s) may output NSFW content unintentionally depending on parameters used. Make sure you tailor your prompts accordingly. For example "nsfw" in the negative prompt.

The purpose of sharing this model is not to showcase obscene material in a public forum. The use of this learning model is entirely at the discretion of the user, and they have the freedom to choose whether or not to create SFW or NSFW content. items.name: Pale Mix
items.description:
A merge of DonutHoleMix and BE-Mix (removed from Civit, no idea why) along with Gothic Punk Girl and Hitoimim art style (artist link) loras baked in

I found that using the mentioned loras with specific strength on BE-Mix resulted in an interesting look, this is that just merged into a single model.

DonutHoleMix was more of an afterthought, and really only because I had to use a second checkpoint to do it in ComfyUI which I use exclusively, but I found that its CLIP model makes the results better and it allowed for a more anime-like model as well

Gothic Punk Girl Lora (strength: 1) helps make more detailed clothing and makes characters cuter, no matter whether you're going for an explicitly gothic look or not

Hitoimim art style (v1.0, strength: 0.6) adds more detail to everything, eyes, hair, clothing, patterns, lace, frills etc. Also dramatically improves some animal body parts like tails or ears, as well as animals themselves. Can sometimes add animals unprompted.

A side-effect of both loras is making the skin more pale than normal, hence the name.

There is also Hipoly 3d Model LoRA (v2), but only at strength: 0.1, so its effect is negligible

The Realistic model should be considered to be the main one. The Anime model doesn't carry too much weight from the loras which are essential to the effect in the realistic model. It is different enough from the realistic model or any of the component models, however.

The Realistic/Anime distinction isn't very accurate, both are more on the 'realistic' side (though maybe it should be 2.5d/3d instead?), the anime one is just 'more' anime and vice versa

Both checkpoints work with booru-style prompts.

Realistic Version:

input: 100% DonutHoleMix

middle: 100% BE-Mix

output: 100% BE-Mix

Anime version:

input: 100% DonutHoleMix

middle: 100% DonutHoleMix

output: 50/50% DonutHoleMix/BE-Mix

The Loras are only mixed into BE-Mix before merging. DonutHole's U-Net and CLIP are unmodified

The CLIP model is the one from DonutHoleMix (modified with lora)

The whole process is done in ComfyUI using the block-merging node

For the exact recipes, load the checkpoint into ComfyUI via drag&drop or load it as a ComfyUI workflow

VAE: kl-f8-anime2 or vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned for both models

Tips:

  • Since there is much focus on fine detail, the results may not look too well on lower resolutions.

The showcased images were first generated in resolutions such as 576x832, 640x960, 640x1024, 512x1280, 896x576, 1024x640, etc., then upscaled 2 times into a second pass with 0.35-0.5 denoising (or hires-fix for AUTOMATIC1111 webui users) followed up with face restoration, then upscaled 2 times again.

  • Don't go too high with denoising on hires-fix. It messes with face structure, especially at an angle, making them uglier. Even 0.3 can visibly change eye/mouth/nose shape. In my taste, always for worse.

ps: don't mind my prompts in example images, It helps with organising them to get the framing I want, I swear

items.name: Internal vore
items.description:
This model has similarities with the internal lora created by JollyLM, except this one is focused on creating both the pred and the prey in the same picture.
The concept is well understood, but an idea often requires several generations if you want to get the internal part right. It is quite iffy, given that this part is not primarily affected by the prompts. It's far from perfect, but the concept is anatomically very challenging for the ai. Inpainting just the internal part with a denoising strength around 0.6 might do the trick if you really want it though, I never tried it.

The model is quite compatible with diverse checkpoints and aesthetics, although it still often pushes its own on the generation. Like my other models, if a specific idea or composition doesn't seem to render well, it might just be something that the lora won't be able to produce with quality.

The trigger word is "internal lora". Long prompts, especially if some elements have emphasis (1.2, 1.3...) require to augment the strenght of this trigger. For this reason, I prefered in most of my examples to keep the prompting relatively light. You might have more success than me with this though.

I'm not sure if input "1 character" or "2characters" make a difference, but the lora is able to generate multiple preys type of picture, even multiple preds, although this is iffy and I'm not always sure of how those two are distinguished.
When prompting, it will mostly affect the pred (the main character), and the prey will often be naked and looking like struggling or scared, because that's how the concept was understood. I feel like putting some prompts like "wide open eyes crying" helps with the face of the prey, and does not affect the pred. For that reason though, it's hard to adjust how the prey looks like.

Using latent couple might allow for more control on that aspect, but I'm not savvy in it and haven't tried it.

I've tried a little to generate some monochromatic pictures, to obtain a manga-like style. I feel like it works well.

Eular a at 20 steps works generally well for most models. I use R-ESRGAN 4x+ as my upscaler at denoising strength 0.2, orelse it absolutely distorts the picture.
I put lots of negative prompts, but they aren't required. Easynegative probably is, I don't know about the others. I put them preemptively.

Although I created it, I'm really no expert at using this lora, so feel free to post your best results so I can learn from you too.

items.name: Realistic Pregnancy
items.description:
While one can get decent results just adding pregnancy to prompts for most models, I wanted one that gave a bit more realism and control over size. Could be NSFW, but it's really meant for clothed, and was created from such examples.

This plays nice with most models and other LORAs. I find it best between 0.75-1. Might want to include "double bellybutton" in the negative prompts as it does like to do that.

Keywords:
preggo - average full term size

just_showing - works best for realistic, just a tiny bump

very_preggo - produces large bellies that would have twins, etc.

ABOUT 'REALISM': Most AI models here are about creating a more perfect version of real. Therefore, your results will skew towards what the model or prompts think is 'ideal'. If you are looking for more realistic skin, blemishes, etc - try using more realistic models + no/few negatives. Most negative prompt embeddings naturally remove blemishes, etc, as imperfections.

ABOUT 'SAME FACE': Same face syndrome also comes down to the model used, the LORA used and your negative prompts. My files are based on realism. If you use a realistic model (Like Deliberate), and keep negative prompts to a minimum, you will get more realistic faces and skin textures. However, you may need to sift through more unusable generations. It can be a trade off.

Prompts that help realism: realistic skin, blemishes, highly detailed. Avoid any embedded negative prompts, and only use the bare minimum.

items.name: TanRealStockings – Lace top sheer stockings
items.description:
The model is trained using a dedicated dataset, focusing on tan stockings with lace tops. The first aim was to improve the rendering of sheer stockings for the Realistic Vision models, where stockings show often problems with lace top appearance.

_____________________________________________________________________________

IMPORTANT: The serie RealStockings is made by 3 different Loras:

-          TanRealStockings, this Lora;

-          WhiteRealStockings, specific for white lace top stockings, downloadable at:

https://civitai.com/models/118574/whiterealstockings-lace-top-white-stockings

-          BlackRealStockings, specific for black lace top stockings, downloadable at:

https://civitai.com/models/124654/blackrealstockings-lace-top-black-stockings

All three Loras can be used together in the same image and make a sort of bundle, providing the same outfit for stockings of different colors.

 _____________________________________________________________________________

TanRealStockings, based on SD 1.5, is optimized for Realistic Vision (checked also with 4.0 and 5.0) but also gives good results with other models, by changing the weight of the model or the weight of the trigger word.

Trigger word:

TanRealStockings

To ensure that lace top bands are visible add in the prompt:

 

visibile TanRealStockings top lace bands

 

To obtain very sheer appearance, specify:

 

 sand color TanRealStockings

To avoid the rendering of garter belt or suspenders write in the negative prompt:

(suspenders:1.3), (garter belt:1.3),

Sampling steps recommended: 25-50

 

CFG Scale: 7

Sampler Suggested:

DPM ++ 2M SDE KARRAS for Realistic Vision

Euler a for non realistic models.

CHECKPOINTS TESTED

Model and trigger word weight

REALISTIC VISION V2.0, V3.0 and V4.0

weight model suggested: 1

trigger word weight: 1-1.1

CHILLOUTMIX

weight model suggested: 1.0 - 1.1

trigger word weight: 1.2 - 1.4

 

If prompt is very long and structured, inpainting is suggested to obtain a more effective result, especially on lace top bands

Effectiveness on more checkpoints will be tested.

On Realistic vision this Lora is compatible with Opentoe heels/sandals with legwears. The use of Opentoe lora is reccomended with inpainting algorithm.

items.name: Gardevoir - Pokemon | Pocket monsters
items.description:
---

This is Tomas Agilar speaking, and I'm thrilled to have the opportunity to share my work and passion with all of you. If you enjoy what I do and would like to support me, there are a few ways you can do so:

  • Ko-fi (Dead)

  • Patreon

After specializing in Gardevoir-related content, I wanted to share some tips for using LoRA models specifically for Gardevoir, the beloved Pokémon. If you're interested in creating Gardevoir-themed artwork or designs, I recommend using the Midnight Mixer Melt as the base model. This model works well when fine-tuned with Gardevoir-related embeddings.

For optimal results, you can use embeddings for Gardevoir, such as its name or keywords like "psychic Pokémon" or "elegant fairy." However, the model can also generate Gardevoir-like images without specific embeddings.

To enhance the vibrancy of colors, I suggest using the WD VAE. Additionally, it's important to set the CLIP skip to 2 to ensure smooth generation.

Weight recommendations for the LoRA model:

  • For v2_offset: between 1 and 0.6 (Only available if you have a strong connection with Gardevoir)

  • For v2_original: between 0.5 and 0.3 (Only available if you possess deep knowledge of Gardevoir's characteristics)

  • For v1: around 0.8

When using this model, make sure to include the trigger keyword "gardevoirstyle" to generate Gardevoir-specific results. You can also try using keywords like "elegant fairy" or "psychic Pokémon" to further refine the generated content.

Please note that LoRA is intended to be used within the context of Gardevoir-related content. It is not a standalone model and is not designed for general image generation.

To use LoRA in the auto1111 framework, follow these steps:

  1. Update the webui by using the "git pull" command or redownload it.

  2. Copy the LoRA file to the "stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora" directory.

  3. Select the LoRA model within the web interface, as shown in the accompanying video.

  4. If necessary, adjust the weight settings for optimal results. By default, the weight is set to 1.

While it may be possible to mix this approach with other styles or embeddings, I have not personally tested it, and it is unlikely to be necessary. Overall, this LoRA model produces cleaner results with fewer background artifacts or irregularities.

items.description:
Older (and bigger) Marlon as promised.

Be nice, have fun!

Marlon Brando (April 3, 1924 – July 1, 2004) was an American actor and activist. Considered one of the greatest actors of the 20th century,[1] he received numerous accolades throughout his career, which spanned six decades, including two Academy Awards, two Golden Globe Awards, one Cannes Film Festival Award and three British Academy Film Awards. Brando is credited with being one of the first actors to bring the Stanislavski system of acting, and method acting, to mainstream audiences.

Brando fell under the influence of Stella Adler and Stanislavski's system in the 1940s. He began his career on stage, adeptly reading his characters and consistently anticipating where scenes flowed. He transitioned to film, initially gaining acclaim and his first Academy Award for Best Actor nomination for the role of Stanley Kowalski in A Streetcar Named Desire (1951). He received further praise and his first Academy Award and Golden Globe Award for his performance as Terry Malloy in On the Waterfront (1954), which remains a watershed moment in the history of Hollywood, and his work continues to be studied and interpreted. His portrayal of the rebellious motorcycle gang leader Johnny Strabler in The Wild One (1953) became an emblem of the era's generational gap.[2]

The 1960s saw Brando's career take a commercial and critical downturn. He directed and starred in One-Eyed Jacks (1961), a commercial flop, after which he delivered a series of notable box-office failures, beginning with Mutiny on the Bounty (1962), which damaged his career. After ten years of underachieving and markedly diminished interest in his films, he starred as Vito Corleone in The Godfather (1972), which helped him win his second Academy Award and Golden Globe Award in a performance considered among the finest in the art form's history, based on extensive surveys of critics, directors, and other actors. With this and his Oscar-nominated performance in Last Tango in Paris (1972), Brando reestablished himself in the ranks of top box-office stars.

After a hiatus in the early 1970s, Brando was generally content with being a highly paid character actor in supporting roles of varying quality such as Jor-El in Superman (1978), as Colonel Kurtz in Apocalypse Now (1979), and as Adam Steiffel in The Formula (1980) before taking a nine-year break from film. The last two decades of Brando's life were marked with controversy, and his troubled private life received significant attention. He struggled with mood disorders and legal issues. Brando continues to be held in high regard and respected.
